  <h1>JIRA Query Language for Writers</h1>

  <h2>1. Fields</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Filter</strong>: Saved filter (e.g., ID 54467)</li>
    <li><strong>Component</strong>: Issue area (e.g., Clearing, FX)</li>
    <li><strong>key</strong>: Issue key (e.g., CAL-490160)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Operators</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>=</code>: Equals</li>
    <li><code>in</code>: Matches values in a list</li>
    <li><code>AND</code>: Combines conditions</li>
    <li><code>ORDER BY</code>: Sorts the results</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Reserved Characters and Words</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>()</code>: Group values</li>
    <li><code>""</code>: Multi-word terms</li>
    <li><code>ASC</code> / <code>DESC</code>: Sorting order</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Term Modifiers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>AND</code>: Both must be true</li>
    <li><code>in</code>: Match from a list</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Functions</h2>
  <p>No direct functions, but <code>Filter = 54467</code> implies referencing a saved filter.</p>

